comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T12:41:32.844Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence: public commitItemMutations covers ordered create/update/close, durable replay, reverse compensation, crash resume, delete compensation, pre-closed adoption, malformed compensation data, and authoritative transaction authors. Linked 8-test gate, built SDK temp-workspace acceptance, packed consumer smoke, and full 100/100/100/100 coverage pass."
  "2026-07-19T12:50:19.982Z",maintainer-agent,"Release-gate evidence: pnpm release:gates completed build, typecheck, docs/skills, static quality, package boundary, token budget, 5,963 tests with exact 100/100/100/100 coverage, version/sync, secret scan, packed-package smoke, and package-first dogfood successfully. The aggregate command stopped only at its intentional Greptile stage because Greptile requires a committed diff against main; the local commit will be reviewed before push."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T12:00:04.589Z",maintainer-agent,"Implemented: public commitItemMutations in NEW src/sdk/item-transaction.ts (exported via sdk barrel), wrapping commitWorkspaceTransaction with correct-by-construction wiring per op: create = explicit stable id AS idempotency key (exists-by-id inspect; compensation close-with-reason by default or delete via createCompensation:\"delete\", both guarded idempotent); update = durable history-marker applied-detection (\"bulk-item-transaction <txid> <stepId> apply/compensate\" messages — field comparison is a moving target and an always-pending inspect would make compensateAppliedSteps SKIP the restore, found via failing test) + version-restore compensation from captured pre-mutation updated_at; close = already-terminal target adopted as applied (never re-closes), version-restore compensation. Results keyed by derived step id {index}-{op}-{target}. 6 specs: atomic commit+replay, full reverse compensation (create closed/update restored/close reopened), delete-compensation, crash-interrupt + resume without duplication (WorkspaceTransactionInterruptedError), pre-closed adoption, input validation. SDK.md example added showing the wrapper replacing a hand-rolled step array. Manual temp-dir verify via dist: committed batch + rollback semantics correct."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T12:00:34.158Z",maintainer-agent,"Transaction-step design learning: commitWorkspaceTransaction's compensateAppliedSteps gates each rollback on inspect() reporting \"applied\" (started && applied). A step whose inspect always returns \"pending\" (tempting for naturally-idempotent updates) silently SKIPS its own compensation — the batch reports rolled-back while the update persists. Any step type whose applied-ness is not derivable from domain state needs a durable discriminator; item history messages are the right substrate (immutable, replay-safe, author-attributed). Marker pairs (apply/compensate, scan from newest) also make post-compensation retries re-apply correctly where a single marker would wedge the step as permanently \"applied\"."
